column4: <parts.title>Hochzeitszug, Northwick Park. [Max J.] Friedländer, [= Die altniederländische Malerei], XIV, [Leiden: Sijthoff],1937, citaten pp. 37, 60.</parts.title>

<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] 40. Korte in houd: Vermeldt een bezoek van FG aan zijn collectie. Op FG's verzoek zal er een foto gemaakt worden van een Chinese kan en van de Bruegel. Reden: cfr. FG lijken de figuren op de kan overeen te komen met figuren op Rubensschilderijen.</parts.title>

<parts.title>[recto] Ad [Addendum] 40. Rijksbureau. Wiener Bauernhochzeit ins Freie verlegt mit Baum rechts, Holz 261/2 x 411/8in, 67,2 x104,4 cm. Slatter, London, Mai-Juli 1949, N° 2; Hochzeitsprocession: 1) Spencer-Churchchill: Sehr gut in Arundel club. Allen wirt überlegen, vielleicht 1912 doch original; 2) Antwerpen (schwach), 69,5 x 115,8; 3) Bacri, Paris, Buchoz [...], ex. sale Mniszech, 9-4-1902, N° 97, ausgest. Paris 1935, N° 19, geht Coll. Aldus C. Higgins, Worcester, Mass. USA, 67 x 121; 4) Paris, Galerie Brimmer, April 1928, N° 822; 5) Brussel 1935, N° 182; 6) Jules de Pauw, 3-4 April 1914, N°6; 6: P. Breughel 1630; [verso] 7) Sale Chillingsworth, Luzern Fischer, 5-IX-1926, N° 14; 8) Sale Osborn Kliny (Stockholm) Christie, 28-6- 1935, N° 13, 271/2 x 41 [?] in. signed and dated 1630, repr. Art News 4-3-1949; 9) Sale Munich (Helbing), 20-12-1917, N° 571, Holz, 73 x 128; Bauerntanz, Wien, ausgest. Museum[?], N° A 385; Der Betrunkene nach Hause gekehrt in Winter, coll. Major Janus Herting, Drummond Mosay of Abercarny, Perthshire, Exh. Slatter, 1947, N° 5, Panel, signed, 76,2 x 104 cm, 301/2 x 41 in.</parts.title>

<parts.title>[recto] Ad [Addendum] 40. Witt Library. P.B.II. Wedding Procession (Northwich composition). Copies: 1) Antwerp Mus., N° 807, Photo [...]; 2) Kling Sale, Christie, 28-VI-1935, signed and dated 1630, Panel, 271/2 x 48 in. (Later exh. Slatter 1943, N° 3: 291/2 x 481/2in. Lent by J. Geoffrey Hart); 3) Brussels Exh. 1935, N° 182, Toile, 141 x 281 cm. Princesse Alfons Isenbourg Bernstein; 4) Sale Chillingsworth, Luzern Fischer, 5 Sept.1922, N° 14, Bois, 73 x 124 cm. Signed P.BRVEGHEL 1623; 5) vorher; [verso] Mniszech Sale, Paris, Petit, April 1902, signed .P.BREVGHEL. 1623. Panel, 67 x 121 cm; 7) Panco sale, Le Roy, Brussels, 3-4 April 1914, Bois, 73 x 121, signed P. BREVGHEL 1630; 6) ?? [sic] 5? [sic] Cutting from Worcester Mus. Bulletin, Nov. 1950: The Marriage Procession by P.B.the Y. This picture, which is dated 1623 and measures 36 (sic!) by 48 inches, will be lent by Mr. Aldus C. Higgings to the Exh. of objects of art owned in and near Worcester by therepr. this is a different picture, judging, from 5.</parts.title>

<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] 40. Witt Library. Peasant Wedding Procession with horse skull in right bottom corner: A) Spencer-Churchill, Northwick Park, N° 116. [...], panel [...] 27 x 45in. Reproduction Arundel Club (In text mentioned versions at [?] & formerly Mniszech coll); B) Without Horse skull: 1) Antwerp [...]; 2) Sale Helbing Munich 20-22 Dec. 1917, N° 571, Panel 73 x 128 cm.</parts.title>

<parts.title>71. Landliche Hochzeitszug. [Max J.] Friedländer, [= Die altniederländische Malerei], XIV, [Leiden: Sijthoff],1937, Nr. 32; [Gotthard] Jedlicka, [= Pieter Bruegel: der Maler in seiner Zeit, Erlenbach-Zürich: Rentsch, 1938], citaat, p. 540.</parts.title>

<parts.title>N. Pevsner, BBC Lecture, 26-I-48 about 'Adoration of the Magi' by Bruegel: The Christ Childe cf. with Lazarus in Sebastiano del Piombo's Raising of Lazrus, The National Gallery; [toegevoegde vermelding]: ' F.G. 1) Query when did the Lazarus came to Narbonne? Was there any possibility for Bruegel to see the picture; 2) The motif of the child also in Titian's Pesaro Madonna (not in the child) especially the veil surrounding the child and drapping on the left side; 3) cf. also Raffael's Madonna di Foligno until 1565 High Altar of S. Maria in Aracoeli, Rome.</parts.title>
<object.title>Doubtful & Wrong Attributions, Copies, Lost Pictures, nos. 43-46</object.title>
